Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "mel" in different forms and positions, with translations in English:

1. *Mel*ješ kafu za sve nas? (Are you grinding coffee for all of us?) 
2. Ova tkanina je prelepa, ali se jako *melje*. (This fabric is beautiful, but it wears out very quickly.)
3. Nismo imali dovoljno novca da kupimo novu mašinu, pa smo morali da *meljemo* sa starom. (We didn't have enough money to buy a new machine, so we had to make do with the old one.)
4. Moramo *meljuti* kukuruz da bi nahranili piliće. (We have to grind corn to feed the chickens.)
5. *Mel* je najbolje uz muziku. (Grinding is best with music.)
6. U mojoj kući se uvek *melje* sveže začinsko bilje za jelo. (In my house, we always grind fresh herbs for cooking.)
7. Kada bi samo mogao da *meljem* vreme unazad... (If only I could turn back time...)
8. Da li si siguran da si dobro *meljio* ove podatke? (Are you sure you processed this data correctly?)
9. *Meljemo* ovaj problem već nedeljama, ali ne možemo da nađemo rešenje. (We've been working on this problem for weeks, but we can't find a solution.)
10. Molim te, donesi mi *meljač* da mogu da počistim smeće. (Please bring me a broom so I can sweep up the trash.)